The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Karthikeyan launches academy 

Chennai: For the up and coming drivers in the country aspiring to enter the Formula One race, Indias lone representative in the circuit Narain Karthikeyan on Monday launched the Amaron-NK Racing Academy. 

The academy, the first of its kind in the country, will identify and nurture young talent and give leverage to the existing racing infrastructure in the country, Karthikeyan said. 

The initial activities of the academy would be held at the Kari motor speedway in Coimbatore. The activities will begin with racing workshops. It will also conduct training programmes for the up and coming talents, the Williams test driver said. 

As of now I am enjoying the role as test driver with the Williams team. Obviously, my aim is to get back into Formula One racing next season as a better driver, considering the present experience with the Williams, he said. 

